$ /sys/power/state

Writing one of the following four strings causes the kernel to transition in the *sleep state* represented by this string:
table { ll
  `disk` ☰ Hibernation (aka suspend-to-disk or STD)
  `freeze` ☰ Suspend-to-idle
  `standby` ☰
  `mem` ☰ Action taken depends on `/sys/power/mem_sleep`
table }

sa:
 `→ Linux/fhs/sys/power`
